processed_reviews: super soft and lovely to wear! i am a bit tall, so the sleeves and hem were shorter than i would have liked, but the color is so gorgeous that i do not even mind! looks super cute with a graphic tshirt and jeans.

it was a little bit small for me. i like to be able to button my cardigans all the way up , but it did not look as flattering as i would have hoped. nevertheless , i am in love with this sweater. mustard. perfect for fall. i could wear this every day. it is soft and stretchy. i would buy this in every color.

great fit but size up. it runs a little smaller. a warmer cardigan to wear on colder days due to the acrylic fibers. it also requires you to handle and wash with care to prevent pilling. overall its a great, versatile sweater and i plan on buying more colors
too small for me. should size up for sure.

unfortunately, this cardigan and i were not meant to be. the medium was too tight in the arms and the bust; the large was still too tight in the arms but somewhat baggy everywhere else. i usually wear a large in most things, but have had luck wearing medium cardigans in the past.
a little small around the bust, but i have a large bust and it still looked cute. love the color!

i do not normally wear 3x but ordered it due to size chart.  normally a size 16 pant.  order the size the size chart suggests.  do not afraid of the number!  sleeves are a little snug, due to my bust size it will not look good buttoned on me, but is fine as an open cardigan.
it was not as loose or as long as if hoped for but it is still a great sweater.
the length and sleeves are perfect.  the knit is so soft.  must order more!  i am glad i got the 2x  it is snug in the bust.
#review contest i bought this cardigan to wear to a college event. the color was perfect, however it fit smaller than expected. it is great quality, so i simply wear it with an open front.

i have a hard time with sweaters because of my shoulders and arms. this sweater provides some stretch, but it is a little thin. the color is cute and the length is good. it makes a nice accessory piece to an outfit.

love. because i like my cardigans oversized i could have gone up another size i think but this size fits perfectly if i want to button it up (i just marked it a bit small because normally i prefer my cardigans a bit larger).

love this! lovely and soft and a beautiful yellow. longer than expected but not in a bad way. my arms are a bit on the short side so the sleeves were a bit of an awkward length but easily solved by folding back the cuffs. definitely buy again in other colours.
run small size up.a lot, other than that perfect
great for layering.  its small access the chest, but i never do up cardigans, so it is okay for me.
it is short and small. very disappointed. i would have ordered in multiple colours.
this cardi is awesome. it runs a bit small but it has plenty of stretch so i had no issue with it.
runs small but i love it. kept it

i like this cardigan, but i am not in love. it is a little on the tight side. i have a larger bust so i am used to that. the color is perfect and i like the length. i wish it was just a little thicker too. i am keeping it though.
i loved the color!  but it was too small for me, so i am exchanging it for a larger size.
loved this sweater so much i ordered a second one in another color. definitely runs a little small but it is a great quality. i normally shy away from color but the yellow was really pretty.
the cardigan is a tad small but i decided to keep it because i think the xl would just hang. the color and material of this cardigan are wonderful.

i wear a 2 or 3x in everything, depending on how snug or loose i want it to fit. i ordered this in a 3x so that it would be a little loose and comfy. however, this sweater was basically like saran wrapping my torso. this runs extremely small!

i ordered a l and fits slightly snug in the arms for me, but not bad enough to send back. i have broad shoulders and usually have this problem with other items. other than this, the sweater is wonderful! it is my new favorite sweater and i wear it all the time. it is made great and feels so soft. i am definitely buying more colors.
quality material, for sure. very well made. my only complaint is that it is a tad too short but that could be because i have a long torso. overall, still my fav cardigan!
it is a little small in the arms but overall i really like it. i might size up for the next one i get though. love the color!

this cardigan is wonderful! the only issue i have with it is that it is a little small when the buttons are together, but if it is just open (how i usually wear cardigans) then it looks great! i would suggest buying a size up from your normal size.
the fit was not right. it ran very small. :(
nice thin cardigan. i like my cardigans to be a little larger. i suggest going up a size. it is a little snug if i button it. and not as long as i would have wanted.
looks great as long as i do not button it
seemed to fit more like a medium than other larges i have
seemed to fit more like a medium than other larges i have

i am probably an xl or 1x, but the reviews and fit description all said the plus sizes run small, so i ordered two sizes up. it is perfect! sits right at my shoulders and hips, buttons easily. the color is beautiful. everyone remarks on it when i wear it at work. definitely considering more of these in other colors!
large is snug on me.  i wish i would have ordered one size bigger. cute as long as it is not buttoned.  sleeves seem 3/4 length.

i love the color of this cardigan. it is thinner or lighter than i expected and leans to the smaller side. if you are debating between sizes you might want to size up. i have broad shoulders which may also factor in.
great color.  cardi runs a little small so i would suggest a bigger size just for comfort.  very stretchy.

so soft. i was surprised at how small it was though; not small enough to send back, but it is unbuttonable. the color is true to the picture, and it is soft and beautiful and flattering. i will definitely be sizing up next time though.

did not notice the plus sizes run small so buttoned up this looks weird. to small for my hips. but open its perfect. so if you prefer more form fitting and to wear it up buttoned then you do not need to upsize.

did not notice the plus sizes run small so buttoned up this looks weird. to small for my hips. but open its perfect. so if you prefer more form fitting and to wear it up buttoned then you do not need to upsize.

i am short and never have a problem with arm length being too short, but they are a bit.  normally, i push cardigan sleeves up to 3/4 length so it is not a big deal luckily. material is a little thin, time will tell if this is an issue. beautiful color!

i do not know if i read this,  but the sleeves are more like a 3/4 length.  i am a size m in most things,  but ordered a l. it fit in the shoulders and arms, but it is a bit loose in the torso, which is ok with me.   i like the color,  it is true to the photo.

love it!  i am usually an 8, or a medium but after reading the reviews i decided to size up to a l.  i therefore have a cardi that fits nicely, has a little positive ease and is not skin tight or pulling at the buttons.  happy with the fabric and the color both cobalt blue and the honey yelloware wonderful.  highly recommend!
i really like this sweater. the only thing is it is a little tight in the upper arms.

i love this cardigan. it is a really nice vibrant color and goes well with almost anything in my wardrobe. it does run a bit small and i cannot really button it up over my larger chest, but i wear it open or belt it.

i am very pleased with this cardigan. i will say that the sleeves are 3/4 length, not the full length i thought i noticed in the primary image.  also, although it does not bother me (because i love my tattoos) but dark tattoos do show through this (and i would imagine other) light colored fabric.  i will be ordering more of these cardigans in more colors.

i love this cardigan. it runs a little small (i got a large and it does not button all the way without pulling). this is fine for me because i either wear it open or with a cute belt. the color is super cute and retro and i will be buying more.

i was very disappointed with this cardigan especially since it got good reviews. the fabric is too thin and cheap feeling. the length was also too short for me. the only thing i liked about it was the color.

i absolutely love the color. the fabric is really soft and comfortable, but it also started pilling really fast. i always wear a small but there was no way i could button this one without looking ridiculous, so i just wore it open. looks and feels great  for a few rounds of wear.

the color looks really nice on other girls but i just did not like it with my skin tone. fabric is beautiful and good quality, but since i have long proportions, i will have to reorder in a larger size.

love this cardigan. i wad expecting it to be longer, but it is not short or anything. also my bust is rather large and i am happy the buttons do  button up though there is a slight gab that you can hardly tell.
super thin material and incredibly tight in the arms

great honey mustard color! fits small for a medium. very fitted designalmost feels like a petite. would need to size up. material is rather thin, but soft. a great item to help you transition your dresses into fall attire. just ordered the large in hope of a better fit.
definitely size up, unless you want a super snug fit.  i never button up my cardigan, but if you do, you may want to size up a couple of sizes if you have a big bust.

this sweater is the perfect mustard color. it is a hard color to find. sweater is thinner than i expected. definitely runs small, so if your a big girl go a size up. i usually wear my cardigans open. if you button it up it will pull and thin out even further. overall, super cute, perfect color, soft, and totally comfortable.

it runs very small. i tend to where a 2x in tops ; 3x if it runs small, but this does not even come close to buttoning. it is well  made and i love the color, but it is also a bit too short for my taste.

i order a small in everything from modcloth, but went with a medium after reading reviews. it fits perfect. i can wear it buttoned up or left open a sit still feels fitted. i have washed my cardigan multiple times and no pulling or fading. i want one in every color!
little on the small side but a nice basic cute cardigan.
i was so excited about this because i am wanting a mustard yellow cardigan. i know the description said it runs small so i ordered the next size up, but it is still small.
this fits very small! i have sent this in for an exchange and have ordered a 2x. i am 135 pounds but like my cardigans to fit just right, not be too tight!
fits rather small. once washed, it would barely fit at all. very good material though, i recommend buying a size larger than what you normally need.
these cardigans are so good!  only complaint is it runs a little small

a rather light cardigan, perfect for spring or a summer night, but too light for a ny winter. i would recommend to order a size up if you plan to wear it buttoned at any point. do not worry about it being baggy or loose?it looks and fits just right. i think i was surprised by it having 3/4 sleeve?keep that in mind, as well.?

i am glad i read the reviews that this runs a bit small, so i bought a size up from what i would normally choose and it is perfect. still a close fit with negative ease, but i wanted this to layer over dresses and tank tops and it is perfect for that. beautiful mustard colour that i think would suit even those who say they do not look good in yellow.
i wear this all the time. it is a but small and it gets fuzzy after a few washes but it goes with everything!

the cut and color are fantastic! i ordered one in small and one in medium and i definitely prefer the medium on me. the small is quite short and i prefer cardigans slightly longer. also, it puckers when buttoned. overall good purchase though!
i am 5ft 7in tall, weight 289, top 22/24 plus size and pants 24/26 plus size, and 44dd. i thought it was a little small i should of gotten a 3x.
this sweater is definitely one to order a size larger. i am a small or extra small in most things and this fits like a small.
very soft. a bit on the small side and it does pill pretty easily. great color.

the fit is odd; i expected this to be baggy on me but it fits tight. which is how i want my cardigans to fit, so that worked out well for me! the color is beautiful and the fabric is nice and soft and stretchy, it is been an instant favorite.
i love these cardigans! i have several of them now. i have sized up from a 2x to a 3x on my cardigans, and they fit great!
runs small so i would want to size up. i would normally get m but went for the l and it fits well
love this color, a little tight  in my arms, but material stretches
this was actually pretty tight on me. i feel like i am busting out of it when it is buttoned up.

i think i am the only person not in love with this cardigan.  the color is stunning, but the fit just does not work on me.  the material is thin and flimsy, and way too clingy.  i usually wear a small, and even the medium is tight and unflattering.  as much as i love it in the picture, i think it is going to have to go back.
i was expecting it to fit snuggly based off the reviews i read, and that is what i wanted so it worked out perfectly! it pairs very nicely with my dark purple dress.

this cardigan runs extremely small in plus size i am usually an xl/1x and ordered a 2x based on other reviews.  it was still small so i exchanged for a 3x and it still pulls at the buttons.  however, i usually do not button my cardigans so i kept it.  that said, the honey is a great color and i recently got this cardigan in peacock too!

i have a few charter school cardigans. very soft and comfortable. the softest cardigans i own and i am a big cardiganwearer. they do run small. i normally wear an xs or a small but in this line, a medium fits best.
this cardigan is so cute!  i ordered the small according to the sizing chart, but it was a little tight for my liking.  i exchanged this cardigan for a medium!  #forgoodmeasure
i think this runs a bit small.  i am normally a modcloth small in shirts and dresses, despite my bust, but the medium fits perfectly. #forgoodmeasure
love the color, and the fit is pretty good
beautiful color. a bit small fitting but doable

odd fit (huge room in chest department, odd given my 10es  i think that is a 3940 chest in us terms?  but the first cardigan i have ever found that sits nicely in the waist  hip area (waist 32, hips around 36 where cardigan ends). gorgeous colour, goes well under winter coats.
the medium was a bit small and the buttons look odd if i button it up. if i do not button it up, it looks great! i really love this cardigan!
love this. i would size up though. it is a little short, and mine shrunk, even with a hand wash. the fabric is still really soft though, even though i wear it all the time and it gets washed a lot.
i love the fit and feel of this cardigan. i am ordering two more colors. i am trying one size up to see if i get a bit more room for shrinking from washing, etc.
i did not keep this sweater.  i am tall and it is short waisted. also the yellow is an odd yellow, kind of like mustard. hard to match.
love this color! i feel that it is a little short and on the smaller side. the quality is great though! i definitely will be getting more colors in the charter school cardigans.

this cardigan is wonderful.  although the length is perfect, the fit is definitely on the smaller side, which is why i opted for a medium.  it is very comfortable and lightweight, and it pairs great over dresses and tee shirts.  and the color is fantastic!  i am very happy with this cardigan and am planning on buying more colors in the future.
i went a size up and am happy i did. i think a small would have been tight, but then i never wear it closed anyway so it would probably be fine to go either way. this is cute, versatile, and cozy.

this is the perfect shade of ochre and goes with literally everything in your closet.  i sized down but it is a little too small for me.  whatever, i wear it at least once a week anyway and get lots of compliments on the color.

i normally take a small or medium in sweaters but i ordered a large based on the reviews. it was still too small across the chest and the litle band in front was a zig zag when buttoned. very unsightly. loved the color though and i am sure smaller chested women can button it and it would look nice on them.

i got this for a gift was am so pleased with it! it is a super cute, high quality cardigan that looks great with so many things. it really adds a pop of color. my only complaint is that the large was not big enough to button over my chest, but that is nothing new.
this is okay.  it is very big and roomy.  i wanted something a little more form fitting but i kept it.  i am sure it will go with something
beautiful color, nice fit but i was really disappointed with how quickly it wore out. i think the quality was not what i wanted it to be.

great cardigan, super cute, well made (cannot say the same for the other colors). it is a little larger and a little longer than i had expected. if you want to wear this with a dress/skirt/pants that come up to your natural waist, you may want a cropped cardigan instead. i kept the small but would probably wear it more if i had purchased an xs.
i love the color of this sweater! it is a little big on me and the cardigan started to pill after a few washes, but it is over a year later and i still love it!

the color of this cardigan is fantastic. it can be paired in so many combinations. the fabric is less durable than i thought it would be. according to modcloth's size chart i ordered a medium, but i think it looks slightly too baggy for the style cardigan that it is. i will keep it though because i do not want to go through the trouble of returning it.
have a different fit experience than some of the other reviewers. my sweater was quite large in the shoulders and waist. i should have ordered the small, but now too late.

the quality was fine.  personally for me, it just looked long and did not flatter me.  i wanted to wear it over dresses; however, it looked sloppy on me.  many love this style, but it is not for me.  i prefer the shorter, cropped cardigan mod cloth has.  i sent it back.
have these in a million colors. heads up  the mustard and the light pink run much larger than the other colors. the smalls in those colors fit more like mediums.

love the color but the fit is a tad big/wide and definitely too long for my short frame. i was hoping for a tighter fit around the waist. however i love the fit and length of the sleeves. a size xs would have been perfect. as much as i wanted to love this, it will probably be returned.
i love the soft fiber! the fit is great and i now own four of the colors with plans to get more!

i have a larger chest so i ordered the 1x. when i got the cardigan it was really big though. perfect as a slouchy, longer cardi with jeans and a tshirt, but it is way to big to wear with dresses and look cute. i ordered the large the next time around and that fit perfectly.
ran big on me wish i would have sized down! but cute color and nice quality

this is a nice, light cardigan. it is not the best quality but it is super versatile. the large is more cozy i think and i prefer to wear it unbuttoned because it looks slightly baggy otherwise. bought this in three different colors and honey is my favorite!
love these cardigans. they run a little big for me.
perfect cardi. a tad long on my short frame, of course, but nothing terrible. great color too !

a large is too large for me. i usually get a size m at modcloth but i read other reviewers and got a large. but i got to say it fits awkwardly. it is too loose on the shoulders. i will be exchanging this one.
this fit a bit large, and was a bit flimsy.undecided so far.
i am petite so i wish this came in a petit cut as it is a little long on me. i wear it with the coach tour dress in noir. it is versatile and easily pairs for work or casual outfits
i bought this a bit big but it is a great colour and quality.

i think i ordered this a size too big because there was not a medium in stock and i saw a review that said they ordered up and it was okay.  i would caution you to rethink this decision if you are a s/m then stick with a m if not then it is okay to order up.
got this sweater in a 1x. almost wish they had an xl available at the time because it is a little big on me. no big deal though! i still love this sweater! the color is perfect.

i love this cardigan. the large is a bit tight across the bust (i am pretty busty), but i do not think i would want it any bigger in other places. it is very soft. too bad it pills so much when it gets washed, even though i always hand wash in cold and hang dry.
i got this cardigan about a year ago and it has held up pretty well. it only goes down to my waist and the picture made it seem much longer, but it is a cute additional to almost any dress.
a nice vibrant yellow. i had this in rust already and i can see myself getting this in many more colours.  it fits well in the waist but with no gaping buttons at the bust.a good wardrobe staple.

i loooooove this cardigan! everything about it is perfect. the sleeves are the perfect 3/4 length and they do not get all stretched out in the elbows like some sweaters do. it ends perfectly at my hip and it is the perfect size. i have a feeling i am going to be buying a lot more of these!
lovely soft material, and the color is gorgeous! the material quality is excellent, but i do wish it was slightly longer. the bottom hits just at my hip bone.

debated 1x vs 2x and went with the reviews that debated the same thing and chose 2x. while the cardi is roomy when closed, it drapes nicely when worn open, which is how i wear them the majority of the time. when i do close the buttons, they do not gape open due to by chest size.

i love this cardigan! i bought an xl because i have a larger chest and i cannot stand anything that feels tight. it was the perfect fit and the perfect color! perfect shade of yellow for almost any outfit. no regrets buying this whatsoever. i am going to collect all the colors now.

i purchased this to be worn over cami's and tees.  i went up a size because of my chest and it fits perfectly.  i can even button without the dreaded button gap.  overall the sweater is a nice light weight topper that will be perfect this fall
love this cardigan. brightens up any outfit and looks great with skinny jeans. perfect length and hangs well on me. i have got very broad shoulders so the l was perfect.
perfect cardigan, i have a long torso so length is always an issue but this is perfect length and nice and light weight. will be ordering in very colour!
fits fantastic over my chest without gaps between buttons trying to hold onto for dear life but still fitted enough on my arms and midsection without being bagging looking.

love this cardigan. it is super soft and comfortable. i goes with so many things in my closet. i plan on getting a few other colors. it does not button up well for me but my bust makes things that button very uncomfortable with their place in the world, so i generally only button half way or leave it open.

material feels really nice but i have only worn it a few times so i am curious to see if it pills and how it holds up in the wash.  the color is the perfect mustard yellow that i was looking for.  i have a large chest and have no problem buttoning it up.

a pretty golden mustard color, but not as bright as the picture shows.  fit gaps at the chest a little, but i plan on wearing it open or with just one button closed anyway.  quality is good, not too thick or thin.  perfect all season cardi!  very pleased and would definitely recommend!

i have had this sweater for over a year and i wear it pretty much weekly. it has held up great in the laundry (although i do not put it in the dryer) and the color goes great with so many things. i feel like it is on the shorter side, but i have a short torso so it works for me.

love these cardigans.  the honey color looks very rich in person, and my chest size is small enough that i am able to wear it open or closed.  the three quarter sleeves work especially well for my long arms, since i do not have to worry about the sleeves being too short.  these cardigans do pill easily, so be gentle when washing.

i bought the 1x because i have a large bust and cardigans rarely fit, but i could have gotten away with just a xl. the colour is beautiful. it is easy to snag though so you have to be super careful with the jewelry you choose to wear with it.

love love love this. i ordered up as many of the other reviewers recommended and it fits like a glove. the color is amazing and the fit is on point. i am a busty girl and i can button this up with absolutely no gaping in the chest area. this will be my go to cardi for sure! cannot wait to get this in more colors!
love these charter school cardigans. i have a very large chest so i have to size up to xl for it to button properly although i also own other colors in l and they fit fine unbuttoned.
not sure about this one yet. i have a short torso and this cardi seems a bit long on me. love the color .

the first time i bought this cardigan, it came apart at the neckline after three wears, and i was super disappointed (hence the docked quality points). however, i loved it so much that i ordered it again, and the second one has held up wonderfully. i love the color and the fit. the material is also very soft.

love, love, love this sweater! it is, literally, the perfect color, just on the mustard side of honey and oh, so soft! i have not washed it yet, but there is been no piling or anything negative to speak of. the v at the neckline is the perfect height, not too low.

loved the color and fit but the stiching came out of the collar part and split the collar part of the fabric before i even washed it. i love these cardigans and have several colors, but i am nervous every time i wear one now. i paid $40 for a cardigan worth about $10. i am so upset about this.
so cute! i love love love the color and how comfy this cardi is. i ordered mine in large even though i wear a small because i like my cardigans to be loose fitting. i want one in every color.

i love the color and style of this sweater and wear it all the time. my only complaint is that the sleeves get really loose and worn in quickly. i like a tighter fit and if i wear this cardigan to my 85, the sleeves are loose and stretched out by 12pm.
great color that went with a lot of things but it snagged easily and ripped. i ended up getting another one though since it fit so nicely.
this sweater was just what i was looking for. i ordered s size up and it fit perfectly. will order other colors
i love the fit and color. it is a perfect office sweater and it goes with all kinds of things in my wardrobe.

i do not tend to wear yellow, but liking the mustard color of this cardigan i decided to give it a try. i like the fit of these cardigans better than i used to (different brand now, i think) and will probably end up buying a few more.
i wear this cardigan with everything! the quality is good and it fit perfect.
read the reviews and ordered a size up. the fit is perfect, the color is beautiful and the quality is excellent. will definitely be getting in more colors.

i got this cardigan in honey and in red and i am about to order it in a bunch of different colors! it is amazing, simply the best cardigans i have ever owned. i like keeping them unbuttoned, i am aware that if i try to button it up this size will be too tight for me. but this works perfectly for my style. totally recommend!
great fit and the sleeves are just right to wear over tanks and dresses in the cooler months. the material is a synthetic blend, which has not pilled at all since buying almost a year ago!

it would be better if it were thicker, but i do like it. the color is a mustard deep yellow. it pairs well with lots of clothing. this is a staple. the fit was like a glove even though i am petite in my arm length.
perfect 3/4 sleeve cardigan!

my only complaint is you could see the pattern of my sleeve thru the sweater. is it because i have large arms, maybe. will i wear it again? absolutely! i usually wear a 16/18 and the 2x was perfect for with my dress. i would not have minded trying a 3x to see if it was less snug in my arms but looked perfect with my dress.

i bought these cardies in honey and purple and am super happy with the colours. i thought when i bought them they would be full sleeve but they are 3/4 on my arms which is fine considering i always roll up my sleeves anyway. i got so many compliments on the honey colour and it really is vibrant. the material is soft and has some stretch.

love.  very pretty color.  not quite so sunny as the photo, which was what i wanted anyway.  fits great, can button up, just do the top button, or keep open.  sleeves are a little longer than average 3/4 sleeve which is great for me as i have long arms.  keeps me a little warm with the extra inch!

the color is true to picture and the fit is great. i find the length of the arms to be slightly awkward. it is a about 12 inches short of being fulllength sleeves so they have to be pulled back in order to get the 3/4 length sleeve look. not a dealbreaker but something worth noting.

such a cute cardigan. can be worn with pants and dresses. very nice yellow, slightly less bright than the picture. the arms are a little longer than i thought they would be, but it looks like a 3/4 sleeve if you pull them up just a tad.

i absolutely adore this sweater! the fit is great and the sleeve length is very flattering. the color surprisingly goes with a lot of outfits as well. my only problem is that it does get a bit pilly after a few wears. but it does not look bad and i still wear it all the time. one of my favorite modcloth purchases!

you cannot go wrong with this cardigan! it goes well with so many different outfits. even though it is made of acrylic, it is a soft feeling material and the ? sleeve is a great length, especially if you wear a watch and bracelets everyday. i loved the honey color so much that i also purchased the navy.

i love this cardigan! i bought it to add some color to my wardrobe and it is absolutely perfect for that. i do wish the sleeves were full length instead of 3/4, but it is so soft and comfortable i do not really mind.

i am not usually one for wearing yellow but this cardigan definitely adds the pop of color i need for my primarily black and grey wardrobe. it hits in just the right place on your hips making it perfect for wearing with jeans or a dress and the three quarter length sleeves are great for spring and fall.

this is my favorite cardigan! i want one in every color! the fabric is soft and comfortable, the length goes beautifully with dresses and skirts, and the color compliments blues so well  i cannot wait to purchase more just like it!

bought this cardigan to go with the main street market dress. while i love the colour, tall girls/longtorsoed girls beware: it is a short cardigan so if you are looking for something to go past or even to your hips, this is not it.
this cardigan is a dream  the length of the body and sleeves is perfect and the quality of the fabric is perfect! i have one in every color!
this is a great cardigan. my only complaint is that the sleeves are a bit short but i do have longish arms! the color is perfect for this time of year!

i am usually a small but they were sold out so i ordered medium and i am glad i did. i like the length and i feel like a small might have not been as easy to later things underneath. color is as pictured and it is nice and soft.
love it, love it. finally bought one of these after reading the great reviews and admiring the colors. goes better with dresses, though a tad short for me when wearing pants.

love this! the color is bold but not glaring, and the fit of the sweater is very cute. the quality also seems to be very good, but i have not had it very long so i am not a great judge of that. seems sturdy but is lightweight enough to wear when it is slightly cool. very pleased with this purchase!

this is a great cardigan which, because of its mustard color, has become an autumn staple for me. it fits me comfortably enough that i have the option to wear it buttoned up, though i typically prefer to wear it open. the sleeves hit me a couple inches under my elbow, which is a good transitional length for the season.

i absolutely love this sweater! it is light yet warm and long enough to be work appropriate. i bought it for a particular dress and i cannot believe how many things mustard colored sweaters match. i receive a ton of compliments on the color. definitely a great buy.
